**who —** The Electron Shells — The electrons' quantized energy levels — shells K, L, M, N (n = 1, 2, 3, 4…), each holding up to 2n² electrons (2, 8, 18, 32), filled bottom-up under the Pauli exclusion principle. Held by the ELECTROMAGNETIC force.

**what —** The electrons' quantized energy levels — shells K, L, M, N (n = 1, 2, 3, 4…), each holding up to 2n² electrons (2, 8, 18, 32), filled bottom-up under the Pauli exclusion principle. Held by the ELECTROMAGNETIC force.

**where —** ATM · The Atom  Framework inputs: the Standard Model & atomic/nuclear physics  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** IS THE PERIODIC TABLE. The outermost (valence) shell decides every chemical property — why sodium is reactive and neon is inert. Transitions between shells cost a few eV → visible light. This is the CHEMISTRY shell system.

**how —** IS THE PERIODIC TABLE. The outermost (valence) shell decides every chemical property — why sodium is reactive and neon is inert. Transitions between shells cost a few eV → visible light. This is the CHEMISTRY shell system.

